            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-68468",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "avahi: Avahi: Denial of Service via crafted mDNS/DNS-SD announcements"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Avahi is a system which facilitates service discovery on a local network via the mDNS/DNS-SD protocol suite. In 0.9-rc2 and earlier, avahi-daemon can be crashed by sending unsolicited announcements containing CNAME resource records pointing it to resource records with short TTLs. As soon as they expire avahi-daemon crashes."
              },
