            {
              "id": "CVE-2017-6519",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "avahi: Multicast DNS responds to unicast queries outside of local network"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "avahi-daemon in Avahi through 0.6.32 and 0.7 inadvertently responds to IPv6 unicast queries with source addresses that are not on-link, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (traffic amplification) and may cause information leakage by obtaining potentially sensitive  information from the responding device via port-5353 UDP packets.  NOTE: this may overlap CVE-2015-2809."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2017-6519",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2017-6519\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: avahi-libs\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2017-6519](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2017-6519)\navahi-daemon in Avahi through 0.6.32 and 0.7 inadvertently responds to IPv6 unicast queries with source addresses that are not on-link, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (traffic amplification) and may cause information leakage by obtaining potentially sensitive  information from the responding device via port-5353 UDP packets.  NOTE: this may overlap CVE-2015-2809.",
