              "id": "CVE-2026-8924",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "curl: curl: Cookie injection via malicious HTTP server using super cookies"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw in curl’s cookie parsing logic allows a malicious HTTP server to set\n'super cookies' that bypass the Public Suffix List check. This enables an\nattacker-controlled origin to inject cookies that curl subsequently scopes and\ntransmits to unrelated third-party domains."
