              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "rpm: Command injection in rpmuncompress doUntar() via unescaped archive top-level directory name in popen() shell command"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A command injection vulnerability was discovered in the `rpmuncompress` utility of RPM. When extracting certain archive formats (ZIP, 7z, GEM) to a specified destination directory, the tool inserts the archive's top-level folder name into a shell command without properly sanitizing it. A specially crafted archive containing shell metacharacters in its folder name can execute arbitrary commands as the user running the extraction."
